testmd

Class TestMD

  • java.lang.Object
    • testmd.TestMD

  • public class TestMD
extends Object
    Entry point class to create a new TestMD test. Primary method to define the test is test(String, String). When running in JUnit, consider using TestMDRule

    See ExampleJUnitTest and ExampleSpockTest for example usage.

    The job of this class is to manage the lifecycle of tests and permutations. Permutations are created through this object so that they can be correctly saved to disk when the tests complete. This class will ensure that files are only read and written once and so it follows a singleton pattern.

    • Method Detail

      • setBaseDirectory

        public static void setBaseDirectory(String baseDirectory)
        Configures the directory relative to the classpath root where the class under test is stored to use as the base directory to store results. Default value is "../../src/test/resources" which matches the Maven standard directory structure. This value can also be set with the "testmd.base_directory" system property.
